<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880418-0162 </DOCNO><HL> Mitsubishi Motors Prices Rise </HL><SO> </SO><IN> AUT </IN><DATELINE> FOUNTAIN VALLEY, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Mitsubishi Motors Corp.'s U.S. sales arm said it increased the base price 3% on its sport-utility vehicles.    The price of the base Montero SP models increased $350 to $11,929, and the price of the Montero Sport models was raised $420 to $14,529.    A spokeswoman attributed the jumps to the rising value of the yen against the dollar.    It was the second price increase on the 1988 models since they were introduced Aug. 31. They now sell for 8.8% more than their initial price. </TEXT></DOC>